# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Persistent Memory System (IMPORTANT - USE EVERY SESSION)

SQLite-backed memory at `~/.local/share/ai-memory/`:
- **memories.db** - Source of truth (SQLite + FTS5 + sqlite-vec + graph tables)
- **MEMORY.md** - Auto-generated from DB, auto-loaded every session with smart context
- **memory-tool** - CLI tool (global command) to manage memories

### Automation (runs without manual intervention)
- **PostToolUse hook** (Bash): Auto-captures failed commands as error memories
- **SessionStart hook**: Logs session start for timeline tracking
- **Stop hook**: Auto-generates session snapshot from git/file changes, runs decay, re-exports MEMORY.md, daily backup
- **Daily cron** (3:17 AM): Runs dream mode, decay, garbage collection, backup, re-export

### Core Commands (run via Bash tool)
```bash
# Basic operations
memory-tool add <category> "<content>" --project X --tags t1,t2 --priority N --related <id> --expires YYYY-MM-DD --key <topic-key> --derived-from <ids> --citations <sources> --reasoning <why>
memory-tool search "<query>"              # Hybrid search: FTS + semantic (RRF fusion)
memory-tool search "<query>" --semantic   # Semantic-only (vector similarity)
memory-tool search "<query>" --keyword    # Keyword-only (FTS, old behavior)
memory-tool search "<query>" --full       # Verbose output
memory-tool get <id>                      # Full detail for single memory
memory-tool list --project WhatsAuction   # Filter by project/category/tag/--stale/--expired
memory-tool update <id> "<new content>"   # Update (auto re-tags + re-embeds)
memory-tool delete <id>                   # Soft-delete (recoverable)
memory-tool relate <id1> <id2> [type]     # Link related memories
memory-tool conflicts                     # Find 50-85% similar pairs
memory-tool merge <id1> <id2>             # Merge two memories (keep newer)
memory-tool supersede <old> <new>         # Mark old as superseded
memory-tool pending                       # Show TODOs
memory-tool topics                        # Generate per-project .md files
memory-tool reindex                       # Bulk-embed all memories for vector search
memory-tool snapshot "<summary>"          # Manual session summary
memory-tool auto-snapshot                 # Auto-detect changes for snapshot
memory-tool import-md <file>              # Import from session summary markdown
memory-tool backup                        # Manual backup to backups/
memory-tool restore <file>                # Restore from backup
memory-tool decay                         # Flag stale, deprioritize, expire (access_count >= 5 = immune)
memory-tool stale                         # Review stale memories
memory-tool hot                           # Show most frequently accessed memories (immune to decay)
memory-tool gc [days]                     # Purge old inactive (default 180d)
memory-tool next                          # Smart suggestions: what needs attention now
memory-tool dream                         # Review transcripts, extract insights, consolidate duplicates, normalize dates (AI memory REM sleep)
memory-tool stats                         # Full statistics (memories + vectors + graph + bridge)

# Graph Intelligence
memory-tool graph                         # Graph summary
memory-tool graph add <type> <name> [summary]  # Add entity (person/project/org/feature/concept/tool/service)
memory-tool graph rel <from> <rel_type> <to> [note]  # Add relationship (knows/works_on/owns/depends_on/built_by/uses/related_to/PREVENTS/RESOLVES/LEADS_TO/REQUIRES)
memory-tool graph fact <entity> <key> <value>  # Set fact (auto-tracks history)
memory-tool graph get <name>              # Entity with facts + relationships + linked memories
memory-tool graph list [type]             # List entities
memory-tool graph spread <name> [depth]   # Spreading activation (find related entities)
memory-tool graph link <mem_id> <entity>  # Link memory to entity
memory-tool graph auto-link               # Auto-link all memories to entities

# Beliefs & Predictions
memory-tool believe "<statement>" --confidence 0.7 --project X  # Create belief with confidence
memory-tool predict "<prediction>" --based-on <id> --confidence 0.8 --deadline YYYY-MM-DD --expect "<outcome>"
memory-tool resolve <pred_id> --confirmed "<actual_outcome>"  # Resolve prediction (or --refuted)
memory-tool beliefs                       # List all beliefs by confidence
memory-tool beliefs --weak                # Show weakest beliefs
memory-tool beliefs --strong              # Show strongest beliefs
memory-tool beliefs --conflicts           # Find contradicting beliefs
memory-tool predictions                   # List all predictions
memory-tool predictions --open            # Open predictions only
memory-tool predictions --confirmed       # Confirmed predictions
memory-tool predictions --refuted         # Refuted predictions
memory-tool predictions --expired         # Past deadline but unresolved
```

### Categories
- **project**: Project-specific context (architecture, stack, deployments)
- **decision**: Key decisions and their rationale
- **preference**: User preferences and conventions
- **error**: Error patterns and solutions (auto-captured by PostToolUse hook)
- **learning**: TIL, gotchas, best practices
- **pending**: TODOs, action items, incomplete work
- **architecture**: System design, data models, integration patterns
- **workflow**: Development workflows, deployment procedures
- **contact**: People, teams, external services
- **belief**: Explicit beliefs with confidence tracking (0.01-0.99)

### Auto-Update Rules (FOLLOW THESE)
- **Session start**: MEMORY.md is auto-loaded. Check "Last Session" and "Pending" sections
- **After significant work**: `memory-tool add` decisions, errors, learnings
- **Errors are auto-captured** by the PostToolUse hook — no manual action needed
- **Session end is auto-handled** by the Stop hook — snapshot + decay + export + backup
- **When user says "remember X"**: `memory-tool add` with appropriate category
- **When user says "forget X"**: `memory-tool search` then `memory-tool delete <id>`
- **When completing a pending item**: `memory-tool delete <id>` to remove it
- **When discovering conflicts**: Use `memory-tool conflicts` to find, `memory-tool merge` to resolve
- **When making predictions**: Use `memory-tool predict` to create testable predictions
- **When outcomes are known**: Use `memory-tool resolve` to update related beliefs

### Advanced Features

#### Hybrid Search (Phase 2)
- **Default**: RRF fusion of FTS5 keyword + sqlite-vec semantic search
- **Semantic-only**: `--semantic` flag for vector similarity
- **Keyword-only**: `--keyword` flag for traditional FTS
- **Progressive disclosure**: Compact by default, `--full` for verbose, `get <id>` for detail

#### Graph Intelligence (Phase 3)
The memory system includes a causal knowledge graph:
- **Entities**: Named objects (person/project/org/feature/concept/tool/service)
- **Relationships**: Standard edges (knows/works_on/owns/depends_on/built_by/uses/related_to)
- **Causal edges**: PREVENTS/RESOLVES/LEADS_TO/REQUIRES for cause-effect chains
- **Facts**: Key-value properties on entities with history tracking
- **Spreading activation**: Find related context by traversing relationships with decay

Use the graph for:
- Mapping system dependencies and causal chains
- Tracking ownership and responsibilities
- Documenting API integrations and data flows
- Building narrative context (chronological cause-effect stories)

#### Belief System (Phase 7)
Track what you think you know with explicit confidence:
- **Confidence scores**: 0.01 (nearly impossible) to 0.99 (nearly certain)
- **Prediction engine**: Make testable predictions with deadlines
- **Bayesian updates**: When predictions resolve, related beliefs adjust automatically
- **Confidence propagation**: Updates flow through memory relationships
- **Calibration**: Track prediction accuracy over time

Use beliefs for:
- Recording uncertain decisions with confidence levels
- Making testable predictions about outcomes
- Learning from resolved predictions (what worked, what didn't)
- Finding weak beliefs that need more evidence

#### Dream Mode (Phase 6)
Autonomous consolidation like REM sleep for AI:
- **Duplicate detection**: Finds 85-95% similar memories, auto-merges
- **Reconsolidation**: Strengthens frequently-accessed patterns
- **Contradiction detection**: Warns on >80% similar + negation patterns
- **Metadata normalization**: Standardizes dates, project names, tags
- **Decay processing**: Flags stale, reduces priority, expires old TODOs

Run `memory-tool dream` after major sessions or when memory feels cluttered.

#### Self-Learning (Phase 6)
Meta-learning that improves over time:
- **Outcome tracking**: Every search logs which results you use
- **Effectiveness scoring**: Calculates keyword vs semantic hit rates
- **Weight tuning**: Auto-adjusts RRF fusion weights based on what works
- **Promotion/Demotion**: High-value memories get priority boost
- **Immunity to decay**: Memories with access_count >= 5 won't go stale

Use `memory-tool hot` to see your most-accessed memories.

